    "body": "This is unlikely to be supported from the core team. I believe that you might be able to compile [lighthouse](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse) for s390x. I saw that the BLS library, blst, seems to support s390x in rust. https://github.com/supranational/blst/blob/29b6b95e26aee872d1793f801f296d076be5b57f/.travis.yml#L51-L54\r\n\r\nNot sure what would be required to support this architecture or how we would test it. \r\nmcl & herumi's dependency will soon be removed, so I wouldn't focus too much energy on that.\r\n\r\nPlease keep this issue up to date with any progress you make. If it seems viable to cross compile for s390x, then we could add this to our list of supported architectures in the future. However, this feature would rely heavily on external contributors as the core team has limited bandwidth to support this functionality in the near future. ",
